20万只口罩泰国扫货记。
China Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Gazette [Issue No.36 2007]
阿茹汗2020-01-31 17:09。
Arjouan 2020-01-31 17: 09.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
图片:首批支援口罩运装完成，将送往合肥 受访者张进/摄。
Photo: The first batch of support masks will be sent to Hefei interviewee, Zhang Jin / Photo.
经济观察网 记者 阿茹汗 1月29日，当地时间5点45分，春秋航空9C8574次航班从泰国首都曼谷准时起飞，它的目的地是安徽省合肥市。
Economic Observation Network reporter Auruhan January 29, 5: 45 local time, Chunqiu Airlines flight 9C8574 from the Thai capital of Bangkok on time, its destination is Hefei City, Anhui Province.
。
.
在机场外，送完机的张进终于松了一口气。
Outside the airport, Zhang Jin, who had finished the flight, breathed a sigh of relief.
对于他而言，这是一次极其特殊的送行：这架民航客机上运送的200箱，10.7万只N95口罩将在三个多小时候后抵达合肥，并从合肥机场陆运至国药控股湖北物流中心，最终将被分配至武汉抗击疫情的第一线。
For him, it was a very special trip: 200 boxes of aircraft, 107,000 N95 masks, would arrive in Hefei in more than three hours and be transported by land from Hefei Airport to the Hubei Logistics Center, where they would eventually be assigned to the front line of the fight against the epidemic in Wuhan.
。
.
张进是洽洽食品泰国工厂厂长，为了这批口罩，张进和他手下的工作人员忙活奔波了整整六天。
Zhang Jin was the director of a factory in Thailand. Zhang Jin and his staff worked hard for six days on the masks.
。
.
20万只口罩！。
200,000 masks.
因为工作需要，张进的春节早已计划在洽洽食品位于泰国的工厂度过，虽然每日都关注国内新型冠状病毒疫情，但因为远离疫区，张进没法感同身受，直到1月24日，年三十上午10点半左右，刚刚参加完工厂春节庆祝活动的张进，被拉进了一个微信工作群，他才意识到形势严峻。
Because of the need of work, Zhang Jin's Spring Festival is planned to spend time with factories located in Thailand. Although he is concerned about the new coronavirus outbreak in Thailand every day, Zhang Jin was unable to empathize with him because he was away from the epidemic area.
从这一刻开始，他的工作中又多了一份新的内容——抗击疫情。
From that moment on, he added a new dimension to his work -- fighting the epidemic.
。
.
这个工作群是由洽洽食品董事长、副总裁、品牌部门负责人临时组建，群里的第一条信息就是要求泰国工厂用最短的时间筹备医疗物资：N95口罩20万只！。
The first piece of information in the group, which was formed on an ad hoc basis by the chairman, vice-president and head of the branding department, was to ask Thailand's factories to prepare medical supplies in the shortest possible time: 200, 000 N95 masks.
张进的手机上同时被推送来更多的疫情消息：武汉多家医院从1月23日开始向社会各界紧急求援包括口罩、护目镜在内的医疗物资，有些医院称现有物资只能维持3-5天，而且求援医院名单还在持续更新中。
Many hospitals in Wuhan began to seek emergency medical supplies, including masks and goggles, from January 23. Some hospitals said the existing supplies could only last three to five days, and the list of hospitals seeking help is being updated continuously.
。
.
口罩告急，八方支援，义不容辞。
Mask crisis, eight parties support, it is incumbent.
。
.
但这么多符合医用标准的N95口罩从哪里来？什么价位？怎么运输？对于张进来说这是完全陌生的领域，一时不得章法。
But where did so many N95 face masks meet medical standards come from? What price? How to transport them? Zhang came in saying this was a completely new field.
不过，任务紧急，他叫上另外两位中国籍同事，一头扎进办公室，开始找口罩。
But on an urgent mission, he called two other Chinese colleagues, dived into the office and started looking for a mask.
。
.
距离接到任务过去两个小时，“小分队”从合作的2家办公劳保用品供应商处预定到了15万只左右的N95口罩，价格为每只17泰铢，之后又临时从网上联系新的供应商，直到下午3点左右，锁定了5家供应商共计5万只口罩，每只价格在15-20泰铢，加到一起20万只。
Two hours before the mission, the team ordered about 150,000 N95 face masks from two co-operating suppliers for 17 baht each, and then temporarily contacted new suppliers online until around 3 p.m., targeting a total of 50,000 masks from five suppliers, each costing 15 to 20 baht, to add up to 200,000.
。
.
20万只N95口罩基本解决，任务似乎完成的并不难。
With 200,000 N95 masks basically in place, the task does not seem difficult to accomplish.
但是公司内部开始拟定合同走流程时，变数来了。
But as the company begins to formulate contracts within the process, variables come.
共7家供应商先后通知，口罩涨价至35-40泰铢不等，还有一家供应商原本答应的3万只口罩被他人抢先，张进本要预付定金，却晚了一步。
A total of seven suppliers have advised that the price of face masks has increased from 35 to 40 baht, while another supplier, who had promised to pay a down payment for 30,000 masks, was one step too late.
。
.
反悔、反复和意外只是刚刚开始。
Regret, reversals and surprises are only just beginning.
。
.
变数。
Variable.
最先涨起来的是口罩价格。
The first thing that rose was the price of masks.
仅一天之后，张进的小分队能够买到的口罩价格普遍涨到了80-85泰铢每只，接近18元人民币。
Only a day later, Zhang's team was able to buy masks at a price of 80 to 85 baht each, close to Rmb18.
不过，在这个特殊的时刻，只要钱能解决的都不是问题。
At this particular moment, however, it is not a matter of money.
张进接到的公司总部的指令是，价格不管怎么变，都要立即下单。
Zhang Jin received the company's headquarters instructions, no matter how the price changes, will immediately order.
。
.
比价格变化还要快的是货源数量。
What changes faster than the price is the quantity of supply.
1月25日早上9点半，一位主要供货商向张进反馈说，无法按指定的量供货了。
At 9: 30 a.m. on January 25, a major supplier gave Zhang feedback that it was no longer possible to deliver the specified quantity.
这导致已经确定的17万只口罩总量缩减到了13.3万只。
This has led to a reduction in the total number of 170,000 masks identified to 133,000.
这时的张进已经开始焦虑了，总是如此反反复复，到底何时才能凑够20万只？。
Zhang Jin at this time has begun to worry, always so repeated, when exactly can make up to 200, 000?
1月25日，张进小分队准备上街搜口罩，沿着大城府（洽洽泰国工厂所在城市）大街小巷，走进每个药店去采购口罩。
On January 25, Zhang Jin's team prepared to search the street masks and walk down the street along the main city hall (where Thailand's factories are located) and walk into every pharmacy to buy masks.
。
.
图片1:沿街扫药店收集口罩 张进（受访者）/摄。
Photo 1: Picture a drugstore along the street collecting masks Zhang Jin (interviewee) / Photo.
洽洽泰国工厂的司机小地是一位泰籍华裔，会说中文，是出门扫药店的主力。
Chong Chong Thai factory driver is a Thai-Chinese, can speak Chinese, is the main way out to sweep pharmacies.
他每到一个药店就会给“洽洽泰国现场沟通群”这个微信工作群发来视频。
Every time he goes to a pharmacy, he sends videos to a microphone group called "Contacts Thailand Live".
其中一段视频中，一位药店工作人员身旁放了一个大纸箱，工作人员一边扫码一边装箱，旁边又站了一位工作人员也在帮忙清点口罩。
In one video, a drugstore worker is shown a large cardboard box next to him as he scans the box while a staff member helps count the masks.
小地随后发来了一段语音，大概意思是，这个药店的口罩全被他包揽了，也有人求他可否匀一点口罩，可是小地拒绝了。
Xiaoji then sent a voice, presumably meaning that the drugstore mask was all his bag, also asked if he could spare some masks, but declined.
他的语气中充满开心。
His voice was full of joy.
。
.
1月25日那一天扫街的成果是1万只口罩，截至当晚8点，口罩总数达到14.3万只；1月26日，周日，张进驱车赶往76公里之外的曼谷，准备去3M公司总部碰碰运气，但是3M公司的库存也已告罄；当天，张进小分队又联系到一家大城府公立医院口罩供应商，答应给到29500只口罩，但是这批口罩并不符合国内医院所需的口罩标准，只能放弃。
On Sunday, January 26, Zhang Jin drove 76 kilometers to Bangkok to try his luck at 3M headquarters, but the company ran out of stock. Zhang Jin contacted a major city hospital mask supplier and agreed to supply 29,500 masks.
。
.
截至1月26日晚，张进已经问遍了曼谷、大城两地大型供应商、商贸公司，总计筹集到了14.6万只口罩，按照原装的箱子算总计750箱。
By the evening of Jan. 26, Mr. Zhang had asked Bangkok, big-city suppliers and trading companies a total of 146,000 masks, or 750 boxes according to the original case.
。
.
张进的脑子里有块小黑板，刚更新完口罩总数不久，又因为这样那样的原因要擦掉，重新再写上一个新的总数。
Zhang Jin had a small blackboard in his head. He had just updated the total number of masks. For one reason or another, he would erase them and write down a new total.
这些不断变化的数字还要同步给另一个工作群，这个群里一共有18个人，其中洽洽的工作人员负责汇总口罩信息、春秋航空工作人员负责航空运输、还有合肥机场和物流公司的人负责货物的清关等流程。
These changing numbers are also synchronized with another work group of 18 people, including staff in charge of gathering mask information, Chunqiu aviation staff in charge of air transport, and Hefei airport and logistics companies responsible for cargo clearance processes.
“我们密切讨论了三四天，包括包装的形式，怎么样才能把春秋航空给我们免费匀出来的14立方的空间利用充足，还有报关流程、货运、对接等，反复更新信息，每个人都积极参与，毫无怨言，”张进介绍。
"We discussed closely for three or four days, including the form of packaging, how we can make full use of the 14 cubic meters of free space that Chunqiu Airways has given us, customs clearance procedures, freight forwarding, docking, etc., and keep up-to-date information so everyone can actively participate without complaining," Zhang said.
。
.
事实上，张进所代表的洽洽食品也只是诸多爱心捐赠企业中的一员。
In fact, the consistent food that Zhang Jin represents is just one of many loving donating enterprises.
自新型冠状病毒疫情爆发以来，社会各界纷纷驰援，捐钱捐物，爱心捐赠地图快速扩容。
Since the outbreak of the new coronavirus outbreak, the community has rushed to help, donated money and goods, love to donate the map rapidly expanded capacity.
根据官方披露，截至1月27日12点，全国红十字会系统共接收社会捐赠物款6.9亿元，其中现金捐赠5.7亿元，其余为物资捐赠。
As of 12 o'clock on January 27, the Red Cross system had received a total of 690 million yuan in donations, including 570 million yuan in cash donations and the rest in material donations, according to official sources.
。
.
感动。
Moved.
1月27日，此前预定的口罩按照张进的要求陆续被送达至洽洽的泰国工厂，张进临时组织工人将口罩原包装拆掉，重新统一打包，这一干就是一整天。
On January 27, the previously ordered masks were delivered to a factory in Thailand in accordance with Zhang Jin's request. Zhang Jin's temporary workers removed the mask from its original packaging and repacked it for a whole day.
重新打包的口罩将于第二天的1月28日运往曼谷机场。
The repacked masks will be shipped to Bangkok airport the next day, January 28.
张进这一忙活，居然忘了预定第二天送往曼谷的货车，直到晚上10点半才突然想起来。
Zhang Jin this busy work, unexpectedly forgot the scheduled next day to Bangkok's truck, until 10: 30 pm suddenly remembered.
。
.
情急之下，他拨通了一位马来西亚华侨朋友，这位朋友此前就已经帮助张进联系过供应商，解决过1万只口罩的缺口。
In his hurry, he dialed a friend of overseas Chinese in Malaysia, who had helped Zhang Jin contact his supplier and work out a shortfall of 10,000 masks.
这次再次寻求帮助，对方爽快答应派车并且免费运送。
This time for help, the other party readily agreed to send a car and free delivery.
马来西亚朋友只说了一句：“现在这个时候能做一点是一点，”张进听罢，心中感动不已。
Malaysian friends just said: "Now this time can do a little is a bit," Zhang Jin listened, the heart moved.
。
.
几天疯狂的采购，让张进无暇静下心来沉淀这个特殊的春节所经历的一切。
A few days of frantic shopping, let Zhang Jin not calm down to settle down this special Spring Festival experienced all.
在送走了第一批口罩后，张进接受经济观察网采访时道出了这几日的点滴感动。
After sending off the first batch of masks, Zhang Jin was interviewed by the Economic Observation Network and said a few days of moving.
除了这位马来西亚华侨外，一位泰国药店老板也让张进记忆深刻。
In addition to the Malaysian overseas Chinese, a Thai pharmacy owner also let Zhang Jin remember deeply.
。
.
在到处扫药店之时，为了能够争取到更多的口罩，张进向这位药店老板说明了情况，此次采购并非个人行为，而是公司的爱心捐赠，口罩将捐赠给中国武汉抗击疫情一线。
Zhang told the drugstore owner that the purchase was not a personal act, but a charitable donation from the company that would be donated to Wuhan, China, to fight the epidemic.
药店老板听后很受感动，当即承诺通过她的个人渠道帮助囤货1万只。
The drugstore owner was moved when he heard about it and promised to help hoard 10,000 items through her personal channels.
不过遗憾的是，因为货源实在紧张，最后老板只筹到了1731只口罩。
Unfortunately, the source was so tight that the boss managed to raise only 1,731 masks.
“这是我遇到的善良的泰国药店老板，虽然没帮上大忙，但还是要感谢。
"It was the kind Thai drugstore owner I met and although it wasn't a big help, I had to thank him.
”。
"
“这真是一个有意义的春节，”张进最后向记者感叹。
"This is really a meaningful Spring Festival," Zhang finally lamented to reporters.
在运走了第一批的口罩后，张进的工作还没有结束。
Mr. Zhang's job isn't over yet, after the first batch of masks were removed.
1月29日那一天，他还在打电话和马来西亚朋友确认一批1.4万只的N95口罩的信息，如果货源没有问题，他将组织从马来西亚调来这批口罩；另外，他的工作人员已经深入到泰国北部的一些城市，继续踏上了寻找口罩的路。
On January 29, he was on the phone with a Malaysian friend to confirm information about a batch of 14,000 N95 masks, which he would organize to be brought from Malaysia if the source was correct, and his staff had already travelled to cities in northern Thailand to continue the search for masks.
。
.
同时，在国内，张进的同事已经严阵以待。
Meanwhile, at home, Mr Zhang's colleagues are already standing by.
他们已经联系好了安徽省红十字会和德邦物流，接到货物的第一时间从合肥机场运抵武汉指定物流中心。
They have contacted the Anhui Red Cross Society and De Pont Logistics and received the goods from Hefei Airport to Wuhan designated logistics center.
。
.
1月31日，第二批N95口罩，将按照这条路线再度运抵合肥。
On 31 January, the second consignment of N95 masks will arrive again on this route in Hefei.
